The pilot reported that he was reading a map in an effort to identify the correct field to spray 
while maneuvering at low altitude in dark night conditions. While maneuvering in a turn the 
pilot did not realize the airplane was descending and subsequently collided with terrain. The 
wings and fuselage were substantially damaged. The pilot reported no preimpact mechanical 
malfunctions or failures with the airplane that would have precluded normal operation.
